HEADWORD: Leuconic
<hw>Leu*con"ic</hw> <pr>(-k⟦ocr⟧n"⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Leuc-</ets> + croc<ets>onic</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Pertaining to, or designating, a complex organic acid, obtained as
a yellowish white gum by the oxidation of croconic acid.</def>⟦br⟧
